uld potentially **use** RDF, JSON-LD, schema.org, or similar formats under the hood, but it is not merely another vocabulary. It is more of a **publishing-and-credibility framework**: it defines expectations around canonical URLs, authorship, typed pathways, entity gravity, and a manifest endpoint.\n\nSo the distinction is:\n\n- **RDF** is a data model.\n- **schema.org** is a vocabulary for structured web metadata.\n- **Wikidata** is a collaborative public knowledge base.\n- **EGGF** is a framework for exposing a creator’s authored corpus as a canonical, navigable graph of intellectual authority.",
